          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript for private or public recitation and prayer in praise and veneration of the Tulsi plant (tulasī), especially sacred to the followers of the Hindu god Viṣṇu and known for its medicinal properties (ocimum sanctum). The Tulsi plant appears in the form of a goddess, Tulasīdevī.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Tulasīmāhātmya</title>
              <title type="vernacular">तुलसीमाहात्म्य</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrīskaṃdapurāṇe prabhāsakhaṃḍe sanatkumārasaṃhitāyāṃ tulasīmāhātmye paṃcadaśo 'dhyāyaḥ 15 śrīkṛṣṇārpaṇam astu // śrītulasīdevītujapratinamaskāra aso śake 1761 vikārīnāmasaṃva[ts]are māheśrāvaṇavadya 11 tad[d]ine idaṃ pustakaṃ samāptaḥ śrīrāmacaṃdraprasaṃna // (f. 29r).</colophon>
            </msItem>
